The paper deals with the convolutional sparse model in signal and image processing, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. The paper discusses theoretical guarantees for the uniqueness of the sparsest solution and the success of pursuit algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also discusses the application of the convolutional sparse model in image processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses algorithmic approaches to solving the pursuit problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
